  Reconstruction steps from (10,11) (bottom‑right). At each step, if A[i] = B[j] the character is taken and we move to (i‑1, j‑1); otherwise move to the neighbor (i‑1, j) or (i, j‑1) with the larger value, breaking ties arbitrarily (here upward moves chosen when equal).

